McArthurGlen Spends EU100 Million on First Greek Site

-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 
2011-06-03T07:40:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/mcarthurglen-spends-100-million-euros-on-first-store-in-greece.html
McArthurGlen Group , a closely-held
owner of European designer outlets, opened its first retail site
in  Greece  at a cost of 100 million euros ($144.4 million).  The site, with a total area of 21,000 square metres
(226,000 square feet), will be located in Spata, near the Greek
capital and  Athens International Airport . It will create 1,000
new jobs and host 110 brands including Brooks Brothers, Diesel,
Just Cavalli, Moschino and Versace, according to a statement
today from the London-based company.  The Athens site includes a “retail academy” to help
brands on all aspects of retailing including pricing. Athens is
the company’s 20th designer outlet site.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
